config TEST_PERF
	bool "Enable OSPI flash performance test suite"
	default n
	help
	  Enable performance benchmarking test cases for the Alif OSPI flash
	  driver on the Zephyr test harness. When enabled, the build includes
	  the test suite defined in test_ospi_perf_tests.c, which performs
	  repeated erase/write/read operations across a configurable region
	  of the attached flash device. Each iteration measures elapsed time
	  using k_uptime_get() and accumulates totals so that average latency
	  and throughput (KBPS) for erase, write, and read can be reported
	  through LOG_INF. These metrics help validate driver performance
	  regressions and characterize the OSPI bus at different clock speeds.
	  Leave this disabled for functional-only test runs as the performance
	  suite extends execution time significantly.

source "Kconfig.zephyr"
